# gRPC Postman Collection Sync

Any **gRPC endpoint** created, updated, or deleted in `backend/apps/*`:

1. Update `backend/apps/frontend-api/postman/grpc-debug.postman_collection.json`.
2. Group requests by service folder (e.g., "Location Service - Port 5004").
3. Multiple examples per endpoint with real seed data.

## Collection Structure

Each service folder:

- **List Services** request (grpcurl list command)
- **Endpoint requests** with grpcurl commands in description
- **Multiple examples** with different seed data

## Service Ports Reference

| Service | HTTP | gRPC |
|---------|------|------|
| frontend-api | 3000 | 5002 |
| location-service | 3004 | 5004 |
| search-service | 3006 | 5006 |
| provider-aggregation-service | 3008 | 5008 |
| tariff-service | 3014 | 5011 |
| provider-adapter-renteon-aggregator | 3011 | 50052 |

## Request Format

```json
{
  "name": "Get Location - Athens Airport",
  "request": {
    "method": "POST",
    "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"id\": \"69be8f97-304d-50cf-af66-ca5df5444ec9\"}" },
    "url": { "raw": "localhost:5004", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "5004" }
  },
  "description": "```bash\ngrpcurl -plaintext \\\n  -import-path /path/to/dist/apps/location-service \\\n  -proto location.v1/location.proto \\\n  -d '{\"id\": \"...\"}' \\\n  localhost:5004 location.v1.LocationService/GetById\n```"
}
```

